        <h3>What is Autotune?</h3>

        <p>
          Autotune is born out of the frustration that kernel tuning
          is a black art. If you are running a Linux server it was
          made for a world where multiple services are running on that
          machine with the kernel giving preference to all of the
          services. However, when running Service Oriented
          architectures you want the machine to be greedy.
        </p>

        <p>
          Autotune optimized the Linux kernel for your application
          profile. Pick a profile for your machine (e.g. Go, Nodejs,
          Apache) and Autotune will set up for the best settings for
          that application which will allow your machine to handle
          many more times the load when it is not optimized.
        </p>
